videos.title: Better Than Nvidia? The Case for Amazon in 2026

channel.title: Rick Orford - Trading Stocks and Options For All

videos.description:
Amazon stock (AMZN) is up just 6% this year, lagging behind the rest of Big Tech. Is the market missing something, or is Amazon actually falling behind? In this video, I break down Amazon’s Q3 earnings, the "hidden" risks in their net income, and the 3 massive growth drivers that could send this stock much higher in 2026.

I’ll also look at the $125 Billion AI spending risk, the "fake" profit numbers you need to know about, and whether Amazon is a buy, sell, or hold at $245.

If you’re wondering whether Amazon is expensive, fairly valued, or setting up as a long-term buying opportunity, this video will give you the full picture.
 
The takeaways:
✅ Why AWS and AI infrastructure could drive explosive profit growth
✅ How Amazon’s advertising business could quietly hit $100 billion
✅ The under-the-radar margin expansion happening in retail
✅ The biggest risk that could derail the bull case
✅ What needs to happen next for Amazon stock to soar

ABOUT RICK ORFORD: I’m Rick Orford, a Wall Street Journal Best-Selling Author and investor since 1999. I help you cut through the noise, understand the numbers, and make smarter decisions with your money.

________________________
What's really happening inside Amazon's 30,000-person layoff? The common story is that it's about culture and too many managers—but the reality is more complicated.

In this video, I share the inside scoop on why the largest layoff in Amazon history is really a capital reallocation story:

 • Why free cash flow went negative as CapEx hit $125 billion
 • How $6 billion in salary savings funds AI infrastructure buildouts
 • What the culture narrative obscures about GPU economics
 • Where every hyperscaler faces the same brutal arithmetic

For tech workers watching the AI labor market, the uncomfortable truth is that human capital now competes directly with compute capital—and the trade-offs are structural, not cyclical.
